you may request to change a normal letter grade to audit(au) or credit/ no credit option. see the audit/ cr/ nc option request on forms page under grades/ grading. the request form is due by the last day to add (add deadline). once add deadline has passed, students cannot change their grade option. once the option form is signed and submitted, student will have no option to revert the audit or credit/ no credit back to the normal letter grading option. no grade points will be posted on the student's permanent record. auditors are subject to the same fee structure as credit students and regular class attendance is expected. view sjsu policy - auditing a class .  only available to upper-division (junior or senior) and post baccalaureate students. the course taken for cr/ nc option must be outside the major, minor and general education(ge) requirements. view sjsu policies below: credit/no credit (cr/ nc) - elective or mandatory phone: 408-283-7500 (select option 3) fax: 408-924-2077 email: general inquiries: registrar@sjsu.edu docusign forms submission: records-regist@sjsu.edu phone hours: mon - fri: 9:00 a.m. - 4:00 p.m. live chat hours: mon - fri: 9:00 a.m. - 10:30 a.m. and 12:30 p.m. - 2:00 p.m. closed weekends and holidays student services center (ssc), window "r" (first floor of north garage, enter on 9th street) hours: mon.- thu: 8:15 a.m. - 4:45 p.m., fri: 9:00 - 4:30 (" " by appointment via qless ) mailing address office of the registrar san jos√© state university one washington square san jose, ca 95192-0009 